article.headline: Chattanooga 83, Kennesaw St. 67
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. (AP) -- Keddric Mays and reserve Kevin Bridgewaters combined for 35 points to lead host Chattanooga to an 83-67 victory Friday over Kennesaw State in the first round of the Dr Pepper Classic. Mays scored 18 points and Bridgewaters 17 and had a team-high seven assists for the Mocs (7-6), who shot 53.7 percent for the game. Casey Long added 12 points for Chattanooga, who led 41-20 at halftime. Kennesaw State (3-10) was led by Shuan Stegall with 24 points, Ronell Wooten with 14, Andre Morgan with 11 and Golden Ingle with 10. The Mocs controlled the boards 41-30. Chattanooga plays Colorado State in Saturday's championship game. The Rams beat Alabama State 61-56 in the other first-round game.
